               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421128-name-1300" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1300" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1300" type="surname" value="BARNARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1300" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BARNARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carpenter, and live at Woolwich. I was in the tap-room of the Castle-inn, at Woolwich, on the 26th of Nov., a little before twelve o'clock—I saw the prisoner come in and take two wine-glasses off the counter, and put them into his pocket—I went up to him and told him he had no business to put them into his pocket—he pulled them out and put them on the counter again.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421128-name-1301" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1301" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1301" type="surname" value="BUNDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1301" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM BUNDER</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Castle Inn. I was in the side room at the time—as soon as I came out Barnard accused the prisoner of having stolen these two glasses—he denied stealing them—they are mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner,</hi> I went in with some poultry in my basket; the glasses were standing before me; my right hand was in my pocket, and the basket on my left arm.</p>
               <p>
